etymologies: early 19th century; earliest use found in Lord Byron (1788–1824), poet. From sensibility + -ous

definitions: Characterized by (especially affected or shallow) sentimentality; mawkishly sentimental.

notes.text: Before the second half of the 20th century apparently only in Byron, and subsequently chiefly used in discussions of 18th- and 19th-cent. literature and society.
